1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,433
<i> Leon!</i>

2
00:00:01,467 --> 00:00:02,467
<i> Leon!</i>

3
00:00:02,467 --> 00:00:04,633
<i> There's strong evidence
against Leon.</i>

4
00:00:04,633 --> 00:00:06,167
<i> The victim was able
to report before he died</i>

5
00:00:06,167 --> 00:00:08,033
<i> that Leon had abducted him.</i>

6
00:00:08,033 --> 00:00:11,133
Juan Soliman's body was found
<i> in your brother's car.</i>

7
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:12,800
<i> I need to come clean.</i>

8
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,867
<i> The police need to know
everything I know.</i>

9
00:00:14,867 --> 00:00:17,400
<i>Unless you have evidence,
they won't release Leon.</i>

10
00:00:18,433 --> 00:00:19,600
<i> Edward, please go home.</i>

11
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,733
<i> Jade, no.</i>

12
00:00:20,733 --> 00:00:21,800
<i> Why is he here?!</i>

13
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:23,800
<i>- Justin! Justin, no!
- Why are you here?!</i>

14
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:25,000
<i> I'm not here for trouble.</i>

15
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,467
<i> Then why are you here?!</i>

16
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:27,800
<i> Man, just leave.</i>

17
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:29,100
<i> Is this about my Dad?</i>

18
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:35,500
Whatever it is,

19
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,767
I'm telling you now,
it's not true.

20
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:39,000
What's not true?

21
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,033
Your father is an animal!

22
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,467
Justin, enough! Justin--

23
00:00:41,467 --> 00:00:43,500
- Jade, stop it!
- Justin, he's leaving!

24
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:46,767
He's leaving!
Come on, Edward. Just go.

25
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:48,733
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [JADE SOBBING]

26
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:50,767
Edward, just leave.

27
00:00:53,867 --> 00:00:55,900
Luna, shouldn't we talk
about this?

28
00:00:55,900 --> 00:00:57,633
Don't wait for me
to call security

29
00:00:57,633 --> 00:00:58,933
to take you to your car.

30
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:00,700
Please.

31
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:06,800
[JUSTIN] Leave! Go home!

32
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,267
[JADE BREATHES SHARPLY]

33
00:01:09,267 --> 00:01:10,800
[FAINTLY] Go home.

34
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:11,867
[JUSTIN] Leave!

35
00:01:19,533 --> 00:01:20,700
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

36
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:21,633
What now?

37
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:24,133
Justin, enough, please.
He left already.

38
00:01:25,733 --> 00:01:27,200
Justin, that's enough.

39
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,200
From now on,

40
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:30,667
you will not see him again.

41
00:01:32,667 --> 00:01:33,800
Go upstairs!

42
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:39,033
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

43
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:40,500
[JADE SNIFFLES]

44
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:43,200
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

45
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:50,667
I hope you're okay.

46
00:01:54,300 --> 00:02:01,233
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

47
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:55,933
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

48
00:02:55,933 --> 00:02:57,133
Good job.

49
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:59,900
Your share is guaranteed
once all this is over.

50
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:04,967
Just keep me posted, okay?

51
00:03:08,367 --> 00:03:09,333
Edward.

52
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:13,067
Dad, be honest with me.

53
00:03:14,167 --> 00:03:16,167
What did you do
to Jade's family?

54
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,267
What?

55
00:03:18,267 --> 00:03:19,733
Me?

56
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:21,567
What do you know
about Leon's arrest?

57
00:03:22,067 --> 00:03:23,100
Leon is in prison.

58
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:24,167
Dad!

59
00:03:24,167 --> 00:03:26,033
I don't know anything, Edward.

60
00:03:26,033 --> 00:03:27,367
What? I don't know
what happened.

61
00:03:27,367 --> 00:03:28,700
Leon is in prison.

62
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,267
Why are the Almazans
mad at you?

63
00:03:30,267 --> 00:03:32,833
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

64
00:03:32,833 --> 00:03:34,700
Is that what's happening?
Did you go there?

65
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:36,767
Is that what
they're telling you?

66
00:03:36,767 --> 00:03:38,700
That it's my fault
that Leon is in prison.

67
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:39,700
Dad!

68
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:40,967
I'm so confused!

69
00:03:42,133 --> 00:03:43,600
What is really going on?

70
00:03:44,233 --> 00:03:45,700
Tell me.

71
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:47,100
I told them you're innocent

72
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:48,833
but they're just
getting more angry.

73
00:03:50,967 --> 00:03:52,900
They're just looking
for someone to blame.

74
00:03:56,033 --> 00:03:57,833
But why does my gut
say otherwise?

75
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:01,933
What do you mean?

76
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:09,200
Dad, just tell me the truth.

77
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,833
Please.

78
00:04:14,433 --> 00:04:15,700
Seriously?

79
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:19,167
Are you doubting me?

80
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,400
Don't you trust me?

81
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,300
It'd be better
if I hear it from you myself.

82
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:34,200
Unbelievable.

83
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:36,900
I'm your father.

84
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:40,000
You shouldn't be
doing this to me.

85
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,333
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

86
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:42,900
[SIGHS EXASPERATEDLY]

87
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:49,800
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

88
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:53,900
I'm sorry, Luna,

89
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:58,167
but Juan telling Justin

90
00:04:58,167 --> 00:04:59,433
that Andy kidnapped him

91
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:01,000
isn't a strong evidence.

92
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:03,833
And with that information,

93
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:08,133
I'd advise not to talk
to Andy Arellano.

94
00:05:08,133 --> 00:05:11,267
And don't speak to anyone

95
00:05:11,267 --> 00:05:12,967
about Leon's case.

96
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:17,900
Until there's no evidence
pointing to Andy.

97
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,333
But how can we make a case

98
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:22,067
if there's strong evidence
against Leon?

99
00:05:22,067 --> 00:05:24,733
First, we need to check
the autopsy report

100
00:05:24,733 --> 00:05:26,367
for Juan's time of death.

101
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:29,833
Then we're going to see
if it matches

102
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:32,167
the time and day when Leon was.

103
00:05:32,167 --> 00:05:34,800
when Leon was.

104
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:36,500
Leon didn't go anywhere
that day, right?

105
00:05:37,433 --> 00:05:39,400
He was just at Hotel 88
and then we went straight home.

106
00:05:40,367 --> 00:05:42,867
Okay, let's ask for a copy
of the CCTV footage.

107
00:05:42,867 --> 00:05:44,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

108
00:05:44,367 --> 00:05:46,500
And besides Justin,

109
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:49,933
we need a witness
who can say

110
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:53,800
that Leon was in the hotel
at that time.

111
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,833
Okay, Attorney. What else?

112
00:05:56,433 --> 00:05:59,433
We'll weaken
Juan's sworn statement

113
00:05:59,433 --> 00:06:01,767
that Leon was responsible
for his abduction.

114
00:06:01,767 --> 00:06:05,133
Because it suggests that
that was Leon's motive

115
00:06:05,133 --> 00:06:06,833
to kill Juan.

116
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:09,433
We're going to question
his sworn statement?

117
00:06:09,467 --> 00:06:10,533
[ATTORNEY] Yes.

118
00:06:10,533 --> 00:06:12,400
Because if it's true

119
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:14,367
that Leon was responsible
for his abduction,

120
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:19,100
why didn't he file charges
against Leon right away?

121
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:24,800
Kidnapping is a serious case.

122
00:06:25,367 --> 00:06:28,433
If Juan was able to report it
after he escaped,

123
00:06:28,433 --> 00:06:31,167
he should have
had Leon arrested.

124
00:06:31,167 --> 00:06:32,767
But he didn't do that.

125
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:36,000
So it's possible that Juan's
sworn statement isn't true?

126
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,000
Could be.

127
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:40,267
But it just clears
that Leon had a motive.

128
00:06:40,267 --> 00:06:42,167
That means
he still can't be released.

129
00:06:43,267 --> 00:06:46,867
The CCTV footage
and the witness--

130
00:06:46,867 --> 00:06:49,000
that's what we need
to make a case.

131
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:52,333
However, if there's any evidence
that Andy was the killer,

132
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:54,367
that would help greatly
with Leon's release.

133
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,567
Okay, Attorney.
I promise, we'll find proof

134
00:06:59,567 --> 00:07:01,167
that Andy was responsible
for this.

135
00:07:01,967 --> 00:07:04,100
[ATTORNEY] You need to be calm
with all that's happening.

136
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:07,967
Anger won't help you
think clearly.

137
00:07:07,967 --> 00:07:12,133
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

138
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:13,133
Is he really here?

139
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:15,567
Yes. He wants to talk
to all three of you.

140
00:07:17,367 --> 00:07:23,967
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

141
00:07:23,967 --> 00:07:25,500
You really had the guts
to show your face here, huh?

142
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:28,567
What do you need from us,
Mr. Arellano?

143
00:07:29,567 --> 00:07:31,933
I want to talk to you instead
about the partnership.

144
00:07:31,933 --> 00:07:33,633
Do you really think partnership
is still on the table?

145
00:07:33,633 --> 00:07:35,867
You know what happened
to Leon, and you think--

146
00:07:35,867 --> 00:07:37,567
That's why I want to talk
to you guys instead.

147
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:39,433
I know the Almazans are busy.

148
00:07:39,433 --> 00:07:42,100
Do you really think we want
to do business with you?

149
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:47,167
This family really
won't stop, huh?

150
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,100
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

151
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:50,600
We were told to stay calm.

152
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:54,333
So this is me
telling you to get out of here.

153
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,200
Go back to your son.

154
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,467
Justin.

155
00:07:57,467 --> 00:07:59,000
Luna, are you allowing this?

156
00:08:01,367 --> 00:08:03,367
Didn't you get a call
from our lawyer?

157
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:05,567
We won't push through
with the partnership.

158
00:08:06,967 --> 00:08:10,067
Maybe you're forgetting
that it was you who came to me.

159
00:08:12,967 --> 00:08:14,533
Is this also
how you treated my son

160
00:08:14,533 --> 00:08:16,033
when he came to your house?

161
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:20,133
Uncle... Uncle, I'm very sorry--

162
00:08:20,133 --> 00:08:23,067
After I paid off your debt
to the bank,

163
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:24,200
this is what I get in return.

164
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:26,067
[MARTIN] The lawyers
will contact you about that.

165
00:08:27,033 --> 00:08:28,433
So please, Mr. Arellano,

166
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:31,467
you are not welcome here
in Hotel 88.

167
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,233
[GIO] What now?

168
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:37,133
Are you leaving or do you want
to be escorted by security?

169
00:08:42,133 --> 00:08:45,133
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

170
00:08:45,133 --> 00:08:52,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:08:56,133 --> 00:08:57,167
You okay?

172
00:09:00,533 --> 00:09:01,567
[NODS]

173
00:09:01,567 --> 00:09:04,667
We need to be careful
around Andy from now on.

174
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,667
All of us.

175
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:14,567
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

176
00:09:18,967 --> 00:09:21,033
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

177
00:09:21,033 --> 00:09:23,167
[JUSTIN HUFFING]

178
00:09:23,167 --> 00:09:25,533
The nerve to show up
at the hotel!

179
00:09:25,533 --> 00:09:27,633
[MARTIN] We need to study
our finances

180
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:29,567
so we can pay Andy back.

181
00:09:30,033 --> 00:09:31,633
What's the plan?

182
00:09:31,633 --> 00:09:37,100
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

183
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:40,567
All we have right now are clues
to a possible treasure.

184
00:09:40,567 --> 00:09:43,633
Which we still don't know
even exists.

185
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:48,667
[MARTIN] Our fathers
didn't kill each other.

186
00:09:48,667 --> 00:09:50,333
<i> He knew something had happened</i>

187
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:52,933
<i> that could have caused it all.</i>

188
00:09:52,933 --> 00:09:55,800
[KIKO] If our father had agreed
to split with Uncle Fred,

189
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,700
<i>that would mean he was
a generous friend.</i>

190
00:09:57,700 --> 00:09:59,733
<i>So, why would he shoot
Uncle Fred?</i>

191
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:02,967
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

192
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:05,267
[MICHAEL] So I plead with you.

193
00:10:05,267 --> 00:10:07,967
<i> Please don't sell Hotel 88.</i>

194
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:11,033
<i> And I want you
to know that it's--</i>

195
00:10:11,033 --> 00:10:12,033
[STATIC CRACKLING]

196
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:20,967
We need to believe that
the treasure exists.

197
00:10:20,967 --> 00:10:23,333
Let's take a look at the
information that we have.

198
00:10:23,967 --> 00:10:25,267
According to Leon...

199
00:10:25,267 --> 00:10:28,567
[MARTIN]<i> He saw Sandro about
</i> to kill Papa and Uncle Fred.

200
00:10:29,067 --> 00:10:30,700
<i>He was responsible
for Sandro's death.</i>

201
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,700
And you, Justin...

202
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:34,900
You said that Juan told you

203
00:10:34,933 --> 00:10:36,900
that Sandro was looking
for treasure.

204
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:39,700
[JUAN] I knew about
the arson long ago.

205
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:40,967
<i> My dad told me about it.</i>

206
00:10:40,967 --> 00:10:43,667
<i> It was a ploy to pressure
</i>Michael Fernandez into selling

207
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:45,700
<i> so they could buy the hotel
from him</i>

208
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:47,967
<i> and keep the buried treasure
for themselves.</i>

209
00:10:47,967 --> 00:10:51,833
And then Leon claimed that Andy
and Sandro were conspiring.

210
00:10:51,833 --> 00:10:54,033
[LEON] Uncle Andy won't
be good for the hotel.

211
00:10:54,033 --> 00:10:55,367
<i> That's it!</i>

212
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:57,833
[MARTIN]<i> Sandro wasn't alone
</i> in searching for the treasure.

213
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:59,233
[ANDY] I'd like to discuss
the partnership

214
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:00,433
<i> with you guys instead.</i>

215
00:11:00,433 --> 00:11:02,733
[GIO] If that's the case,
then they have a common goal.

216
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:06,233
The treasure hidden somewhere
at Hotel 88.

217
00:11:06,233 --> 00:11:08,067
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:09,200
[KIKO] Gio...

219
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:11,667
I-I don't like where
this is going.

220
00:11:12,333 --> 00:11:14,667
[GIO] Let's assume that
the treasure is real

221
00:11:14,667 --> 00:11:16,967
and that Andy and Sandro
were in cahoots.

222
00:11:19,367 --> 00:11:22,767
Also, that Roi didn't kill
our fathers.

223
00:11:22,767 --> 00:11:26,033
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:11:26,033 --> 00:11:29,367
So, Uncle Andy had something
with their deaths?

225
00:11:31,033 --> 00:11:32,133
Yes.

226
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:37,200
That's why Andy
implicated Leon.

227
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:42,200
He framed him
so he could get Hotel 88.

228
00:11:42,233 --> 00:11:43,067
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:11:43,067 --> 00:11:45,367
To find the treasure
hidden here.

230
00:11:45,367 --> 00:11:48,200
So, are you saying that Andy
is the brains behind all this?

231
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:53,000
[JUSTIN] But how can we
make him pay for his crimes?

232
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,933
We need to find the treasure.

233
00:11:57,367 --> 00:12:04,333
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

234
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:11,400
When we find the treasure,

235
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,100
Andy will come after us.

236
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:17,400
He could do to us exactly
what he did to our fathers.

237
00:12:19,767 --> 00:12:21,933
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

238
00:12:21,933 --> 00:12:24,833
We'll count on him doing that
so we can catch him.

239
00:12:25,867 --> 00:12:27,900
We'll use ourselves as bait?

240
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,967
[MARTIN] That means...

241
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:34,267
our lives will be in danger.

242
00:12:36,433 --> 00:12:38,233
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:12:38,233 --> 00:12:42,133
If that's the price of truth
and justice for our fathers,

244
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:47,133
then I'm all in.

245
00:12:50,167 --> 00:12:51,233
You?

246
00:12:52,367 --> 00:12:53,433
Of course.

247
00:12:54,467 --> 00:12:55,900
Me too.

248
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:58,533
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:12:58,533 --> 00:13:00,267
For Dad and Leon.

250
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:06,000
So let's begin our search
for this treasure.

251
00:13:22,233 --> 00:13:23,533
Sir, sir, sir, sir.

252
00:13:24,867 --> 00:13:26,233
Hey, boss, what's the problem?

253
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:28,467
About the guy who died
at the other corner,

254
00:13:28,467 --> 00:13:30,367
the same man who was found
in Almazan's car...

255
00:13:31,133 --> 00:13:32,300
Did you know Juan?

256
00:13:33,033 --> 00:13:34,067
But I did see one thing.

257
00:13:34,067 --> 00:13:36,167
Someone else was speaking
with the young man.

258
00:13:36,167 --> 00:13:38,800
Come on, mister. Don't believe
whatever rumor you hear.

259
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,133
I'm telling the truth.

260
00:13:40,133 --> 00:13:42,533
I have a video.
It really wasn't Leon.

261
00:13:42,533 --> 00:13:45,567
Hey, hey, hey! You again?
Go away!

262
00:13:45,567 --> 00:13:47,867
You think I don't know what
they say about you

263
00:13:47,867 --> 00:13:48,867
and your drug habit?

264
00:13:48,867 --> 00:13:50,133
Next time, I'll arrest you!

265
00:13:50,133 --> 00:13:51,400
Now, scram!

266
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

267
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:56,033
He's bullying folks here
so they'll buy his stuff.

268
00:13:58,433 --> 00:14:00,400
Alright, I just have
to finish something.

269
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:12,567
[GRUNTING]

270
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:15,600
What do you want from me?

271
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,433
- Let me go!
- Be quiet!

272
00:14:17,433 --> 00:14:19,033
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

273
00:14:19,033 --> 00:14:20,133
What's going on?

274
00:14:22,467 --> 00:14:23,867
Thank you, boss.

275
00:14:25,233 --> 00:14:27,233
You have a video of Juan
and that Almazan guy?

276
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:28,533
I'm an addict, remember?

277
00:14:28,567 --> 00:14:30,000
Where is it? Where's the video?

278
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,200
- I have it.
- Where? Give it to me!

279
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,133
That's it?
I don't get anything for it?

280
00:14:34,133 --> 00:14:36,633
You'll get this if you don't
hand it over right now.

281
00:14:36,633 --> 00:14:43,567
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

282
00:14:48,567 --> 00:14:50,100
Justin Almazan?

283
00:14:56,267 --> 00:14:57,967
Go ahead, snitch.

284
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,033
You know what'll happen.

285
00:15:00,033 --> 00:15:06,967
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

286
00:15:22,967 --> 00:15:24,333
[LUNA] What are we
going to do with these?

287
00:15:25,267 --> 00:15:28,000
[GIO] We need to figure out
what these mean.

288
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,433
Do you think those are clues?

289
00:15:29,433 --> 00:15:31,600
Yeah. Whether it's true or not,

290
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,333
whether there's treasure or not,

291
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:36,200
this could lead us to the truth.

292
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,600
About Papa's video...

293
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,333
It was cut, Kiko.

294
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:42,667
What else can we get from that?

295
00:15:42,667 --> 00:15:44,533
Maybe he mentioned
some clues there.

296
00:15:44,533 --> 00:15:46,567
Or anything that could help us.

297
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,033
Maybe he said it
in the missing part.

298
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:55,567
Okay.

299
00:15:55,567 --> 00:15:58,667
I'll try to fix it
or have someone fix it.

300
00:15:58,667 --> 00:16:00,233
There's no harm
in trying, right?

301
00:16:02,467 --> 00:16:03,767
I'll help Kiko.

302
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:07,333
Fine.

303
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:10,400
Here. You and Jade read the book

304
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:12,567
and look for whatever clues
are in there.

305
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:14,400
[GIO] I'll handle the compass.

306
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:16,200
[LUNA] I'll help you.

307
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:21,733
Papa has one like that,
so I know how to use it.

308
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:25,033
- Okay.
- Okay.

309
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:28,333
Then I'll handle the monocular.

310
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,733
Martin, I'm sorry.

311
00:16:30,733 --> 00:16:31,767
Sorry.

312
00:16:32,767 --> 00:16:35,367
We just wanted to help Justin.

313
00:16:35,367 --> 00:16:37,533
Trixie, what you did
was really dangerous.

314
00:16:38,067 --> 00:16:39,567
What if Dad finds out--

315
00:16:40,267 --> 00:16:43,533
He won't find out
because you won't tell him.

316
00:16:43,567 --> 00:16:46,500
If you tell him about this,
you'll just get scolded too.

317
00:16:46,767 --> 00:16:48,500
[INHALES] Fine.

318
00:16:48,767 --> 00:16:51,633
But Trixie, you're seriously
not leaving this hotel anymore.

319
00:16:52,333 --> 00:16:53,367
Okay?

320
00:16:53,667 --> 00:16:55,333
What am I supposed to do here?

321
00:16:56,533 --> 00:16:58,333
Keep yourself safe.

322
00:16:58,333 --> 00:17:00,767
If you can't do that,
just go back to Manila.

323
00:17:00,767 --> 00:17:02,400
You'll be safer there.

324
00:17:03,633 --> 00:17:07,467
Fine, okay.
I won't leave the hotel.

325
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:09,833
Okay.

326
00:17:11,733 --> 00:17:12,800
I'm sorry.

327
00:17:13,433 --> 00:17:16,333
- Kiko, I'm sorry!
- Ouch!

328
00:17:16,367 --> 00:17:17,600
I'm sorry!

329
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,300
- Cheska!
- Maybe-- Maybe...

330
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:20,600
it'll work if I sweet-talk you.

331
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:22,333
- Sorry.
- You're so stubborn.

332
00:17:22,733 --> 00:17:24,700
We don't do that in this family.

333
00:17:25,333 --> 00:17:26,800
- [SIGHS]
- That won't work on me.

334
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:29,700
Kiko, I'm sorry.

335
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:33,433
We just wanted to help Justin.

336
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:35,833
We felt bad because
he's doing this solo.

337
00:17:36,567 --> 00:17:39,400
But, Cheska, what he's doing
is really dangerous.

338
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:42,800
This isn't just about vlogging
paranormal stuff anymore.

339
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:44,367
There are dangerous people

340
00:17:44,367 --> 00:17:45,867
who could hurt you
if you get caught.

341
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:48,833
Kiko, you said it yourself,
right?

342
00:17:49,533 --> 00:17:51,333
You said it's dangerous.

343
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,300
And he's all alone.

344
00:17:54,867 --> 00:17:58,333
At least with us, even if we
do things our own way,

345
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:00,733
we've got each other's backs.

346
00:18:02,333 --> 00:18:03,800
Justin's different.

347
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:07,767
He has no one helping him.

348
00:18:10,567 --> 00:18:12,867
So go ahead, Kiko...

349
00:18:12,867 --> 00:18:15,600
I'll accept it if you punish me.

350
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:17,700
If you order me to do something,
I'll do anything.

351
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:20,500
But I won't obey you
on this one.

352
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:21,767
I'm not going back to Mama.

353
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:24,633
You already have too much
on your mind here

354
00:18:24,633 --> 00:18:25,867
for me to leave you alone.

355
00:18:30,533 --> 00:18:31,767
Okay.

356
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:35,367
Since you're already
staying here at the hotel,

357
00:18:35,367 --> 00:18:37,367
help out with running the place

358
00:18:37,667 --> 00:18:39,333
while we take care
of some things.

359
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:42,300
Of course, Kiko.
I'm game for that.

360
00:18:42,300 --> 00:18:43,400
Thank you, Kiko.

361
00:18:49,500 --> 00:18:50,667
By the way, Kiko...

362
00:18:51,300 --> 00:18:54,267
Hmm? What is it?

363
00:18:57,400 --> 00:19:01,533
That's the map we got
from Sandro's house.

364
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:04,900
Kiko, we've already been there.

365
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:09,833
But maybe it'll be more useful
if you keep it.

366
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:16,500
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:17,600
[JUSTIN] Cheska!

368
00:19:18,433 --> 00:19:20,367
- [CHESKA] Justin!
- [TRIXIE] Justin...

369
00:19:20,767 --> 00:19:22,467
There's something
I want to check.

370
00:19:22,467 --> 00:19:24,400
I need to scan the videos
you took.

371
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:26,700
Maybe you captured something
we can use as evidence

372
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,400
against Leon's case.

373
00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:30,300
Oh, okay.

374
00:19:31,633 --> 00:19:32,600
Uh...

375
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:34,567
Kiko, I'm just helping out.

376
00:19:35,533 --> 00:19:36,633
It's only videos.

377
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:38,867
Besides, we're staying here
at the hotel anyway.

378
00:19:38,867 --> 00:19:40,567
That's okay, right?

379
00:19:40,567 --> 00:19:41,667
Please, Kiko.

380
00:19:42,733 --> 00:19:43,767
Fine.

381
00:19:44,567 --> 00:19:45,933
- Thank you, Kiko.
- Just stay here.

382
00:19:45,933 --> 00:19:47,300
Mh-mm.

383
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,867
Martin, I'll help too, okay?

384
00:19:52,867 --> 00:19:54,833
I won't leave the hotel,
promise.

385
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,800
- I literally just said that.
- I know.

386
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,333
I'll listen this time.

387
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,800
- Go.
- See you later, Martin.

388
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:04,633
- Come on.
- Thank you, Kiko.

389
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:06,833
Come on.

390
00:20:14,467 --> 00:20:15,667
There's nothing.

391
00:20:15,667 --> 00:20:17,567
That's really everything,
Justin.

392
00:20:18,867 --> 00:20:20,533
It's all there already,
the market,

393
00:20:20,533 --> 00:20:22,633
- the abandoned building...
- Hmm.

394
00:20:22,633 --> 00:20:24,433
Juan's father's house.

395
00:20:24,433 --> 00:20:25,467
You guys are unbelievable!

396
00:20:25,467 --> 00:20:26,533
At first, you didn't want me
recording videos,

397
00:20:26,533 --> 00:20:28,300
and now you're asking me
for videos.

398
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,533
If I had known
this would happen,

399
00:20:30,533 --> 00:20:31,667
I wouldn't have stopped you.

400
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:33,633
There has to be something.

401
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,367
[BREATHES DEEPLY]
Let's take a break first.

402
00:20:36,633 --> 00:20:37,367
I'm going to grab a drink.

403
00:20:37,367 --> 00:20:38,833
My eyes are starting to hurt.

404
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:40,700
Okay.

405
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:45,833
[TRIXIE] Hey,
we're taking a break, right?

406
00:20:46,733 --> 00:20:48,467
We need to find something,
Trixie.

407
00:20:48,733 --> 00:20:49,867
Yeah, I know.

408
00:20:49,867 --> 00:20:51,567
But you can rest for a bit.

409
00:20:51,567 --> 00:20:52,567
I can't!

410
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,567
This is for my brother.

411
00:20:58,700 --> 00:20:59,967
Justin...

412
00:21:01,367 --> 00:21:03,467
It's not your fault
your brother got imprisoned.

413
00:21:03,467 --> 00:21:04,800
I'm the one who knew Juan.

414
00:21:05,567 --> 00:21:07,533
I'm the one who knew about
Uncle Andy's involvement

415
00:21:07,533 --> 00:21:08,600
in all this.

416
00:21:09,567 --> 00:21:11,033
I got myself involved.

417
00:21:12,767 --> 00:21:15,667
If you hadn't looked into what
was happening to your brother,

418
00:21:15,667 --> 00:21:17,533
things could've ended up
even worse.

419
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:21,100
You're doing all of this
to protect them, right?

420
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:24,733
Your brother,
and Jade and Luna too.

421
00:21:24,733 --> 00:21:25,667
Am I right?

422
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,367
So please...

423
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:30,533
Don't be too hard
on yourself, okay?

424
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:33,333
Justin, none of this
is your fault.

425
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:39,467
I promise, Trixie, I'll do
everything I can to free Leon.

426
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:41,933
I know.

427
00:21:42,767 --> 00:21:45,133
And I know you're
not giving up either.

428
00:21:45,133 --> 00:21:51,933
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

429
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:01,967
That's Justin, right?

430
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:06,500
He's talking to the victim
they found behind your car.

431
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:13,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

432
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:18,000
Sis, don't you have
anything else to do?

433
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,967
Why are you doing
housekeeping work?

434
00:22:19,967 --> 00:22:21,667
Hey, I'm not slacking off, okay?

435
00:22:21,667 --> 00:22:24,433
Sir Martin actually left me
a lot of things to do.

436
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:28,067
I'm just sad because I'm alone.

437
00:22:28,867 --> 00:22:31,067
What was that?
Why are you sad?

438
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:35,200
Because I'm not with Sir Martin.

439
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:36,800
I miss him.

440
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:40,667
[CHUCKLES]
You said what, Sari?

441
00:22:42,533 --> 00:22:44,600
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]
Uh, what I meant, Miss Trixie...

442
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:47,933
I miss Sir--

443
00:22:47,933 --> 00:22:49,733
I mean, Sir's aura.

444
00:22:49,767 --> 00:22:51,600
- I miss his aura.
- Ah, just his aura.

445
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:54,233
I'm just used to always
being bossed around.

446
00:22:54,233 --> 00:22:56,667
- That's all.
- Ah, she used to it.

447
00:22:56,667 --> 00:23:00,600
[TRIXIE LAUGHS] Okay.
If you say so.

448
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,500
Trixie, Cheska, maybe
you want something to eat.

449
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:03,667
I cooked some snacks.

450
00:23:03,667 --> 00:23:06,233
Make it for three, Monette.
Include Sir Justin too.

451
00:23:06,233 --> 00:23:07,967
Oh, Justin already went home.

452
00:23:07,967 --> 00:23:09,433
He's staying at their house
for now.

453
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:12,833
Oh no, maybe they haven't
even thought about eating

454
00:23:12,833 --> 00:23:13,967
because of what happened.

455
00:23:14,733 --> 00:23:17,200
- [LOUD CLATTER]
- [MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

456
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:19,533
What was that?
Did you hear that?

457
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:21,733
Yeah, where did that come from?

458
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:23,100
[RAPHIE] Maybe it's a guest?

459
00:23:23,100 --> 00:23:24,200
What was that?

460
00:23:24,833 --> 00:23:25,900
Did you hear that?

461
00:23:25,900 --> 00:23:32,900
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

462
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:52,800
[EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES]

463
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:53,833
[SANDRO] Juan...

464
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:56,533
Juan...

465
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,000
My son...

466
00:24:03,300 --> 00:24:06,867
Who killed you?!

467
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:15,733
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

468
00:24:15,733 --> 00:24:16,867
<i> That's Justin, right?</i>

469
00:24:16,867 --> 00:24:18,267
<i>I can keep this
with me forever.</i>

470
00:24:18,267 --> 00:24:19,633
But there's something in return.

471
00:24:19,633 --> 00:24:20,867
<i> He's playing games now.</i>

472
00:24:20,867 --> 00:24:22,833
<i> We'll play along too.</i>

473
00:24:22,833 --> 00:24:24,100
That Andy guy probably thinks

474
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:25,133
<i> he's the only one
who can fool people.</i>

475
00:24:25,133 --> 00:24:26,667
<i> Well, let him try us.</i>

476
00:24:26,667 --> 00:24:28,200
<i>You're going to become
the hotel's partner.</i>

477
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,800
<i> This isn't just Andy.</i>

478
00:24:29,833 --> 00:24:31,700
<i>I'm sure he has a
powerful accomplice</i>

479
00:24:31,700 --> 00:24:32,967
<i> helping him put me in jail.</i>

480
00:24:32,967 --> 00:24:33,967
<i> An accomplice?</i>

481
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:36,300
Look at this, it's cut short.

482
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:38,300
<i>- Like, corrupted?
- Yeah.</i>

483
00:24:39,133 --> 00:24:41,033
<i>We have something
else we can offer you.</i>

484
00:24:41,033 --> 00:24:42,033
<i> What is it?</i>

485
00:24:42,033 --> 00:24:44,900
Clues about the hidden treasure.

486
00:24:45,733 --> 00:24:48,267
<i> I'll help you search
for the treasure.</i>

487
00:24:56,067 --> 00:24:57,300
<i> He's alive.</i>

488
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:59,567
He's just here on the island.
